        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1990-05-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1990-05-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="117"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d117">
                <head>117. Memorandum From the President’s Assistant for National Security Affairs
                        (<persName corresp="#p_SB_1">Scowcroft</persName>) to President Bush<note
                        n="1" type="source" xml:id="d117fn1">Source: <persName corresp="#p_BGHW_1"
                            >George H.W. Bush</persName> Library, <persName corresp="#p_BGHW_1"
                            >Bush</persName> Presidential Records, National Security Council,
                        H-Files, NSD Files, OA/ID 90004–014, NSD–40—May 14, 1990—Decisions on START
                        Issues. Secret. Sent for action. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_KAL_1"
                            >Kanter</persName>. Copied to Quayle and <persName corresp="#p_SJH_1"
                            >Sununu</persName>. A stamped notation indicates <persName
                            corresp="#p_BGHW_1">Bush</persName> saw the memorandum on May 14.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1990-05-14">May 14, 1990</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Proposed National Security Directive (NSD) on <gloss target="#t_START_1"
                            >START</gloss>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p rend="sectiontitleital">Purpose</p>
                <p>To seek your approval of a proposed National Security Directive providing U.S.
                    positions on several <gloss target="#t_START_1">START</gloss> issues.</p>
                <p rend="sectiontitleital">Background</p>
                <p>I have reviewed the major issues that remain in <gloss target="#t_START_1"
                        >START</gloss> with <persName corresp="#p_BJA_1">Jim Baker</persName>,
                        <persName corresp="#p_CRB_1">Dick Cheney</persName>, and <persName
                        corresp="#p_PCL_1">Colin Powell</persName>. They concur in the proposed NSD
                    (attached at Tab A) that defines the U.S. positions Jim should be prepared to
                    take at the Moscow ministerial in an effort to reach closure with the Soviets on
                    the basic <gloss target="#t_START_1">START</gloss> agreement by the Summit.</p>
                <p rend="sectiontitleital">RECOMMENDATION</p>
                <p>That you sign the proposed NSD at Tab A.<note n="2" xml:id="d117fn2">Printed as
                            <ref target="#d119">Document 119</ref>.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
